<br>
First, let me say that of all the people I've met on this server, your name is the most respected in my mind.  I've always felt that the idea of the Traders Union is a fantastic one, and you seem to me to be the epitome of a fair salesman.<br>
<br>
That said, I'm a little confused about how this unnamed person (I think I know who she might be--there's someone who's been undercutting my prices on Raw Silk fairly consistently, sellling it for just barely over what I can sell it back to NPC Merchants for) is making a profit off of jewellry you've made for her, unless you sold her the jewellry at a discount in the first place.<br>
<br>
It sounds like, to me, that what she's done is set up shop and is charging lower prices than you are in order to drum up business.  That's free market capitalism for you.  Either you lower your prices to compete with her, or you rely on your reputation and clout to maintain your prices (and probably lose some customers to her).<br>
<br>
If you spent some time selling at just above cost, turning only a slight profit, you might be able to undercut her efforts.  But it sounds to me like this is more of a trade war than something unethical.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen, Sixteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare, Tailor/Potter/Blacksmith (and I might open a Grocery Store, with the amount of veggies and fruits I lug around with me) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 12/16/01 3:33:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/01 4:29:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=908.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying Low, Selling High</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry, I should have been more specific.  In fact, she is selling at quite a bit more than I do, but doing it when I'm not there.  The trade-crafted items are a small part of this issue, it's just what rankles me the most personally.  It's more a question of found items which have less of a fixed price.  She's buying them cheaply when she can, off people who take pity on a lower-leveled character, then selling them for every coin she can get later on.  I still don't know how I should feel about it.  More opinions are sought after.<br>
